  "summary": "Disguised with a mustache, a suit, and a changed voice, Bobby checks into the Stafely Angler Arms Hotel under the persona of Edward Hawkins, a chauffeur for a Miss Francis DeVenture. While at the inn, he speaks with the proprietor, Thomas Ashe, and other locals. Ashe mentions that a young man named Mr. Rives witnessed a recent car accident involving Miss Deveraux.\n\nThe conversation turns to the Grantham Sanatorium, run by an American doctor named Nicholson. The villagers express deep suspicion and fear regarding the facility. A barmaid recounts a story about a wealthy young girl who attempted to escape the sanatorium, claiming she was being held against her will despite being diagnosed with delusions of persecution.\n\nSeeking more information, Bobby walks toward the Grantham Sanatorium and enters the grounds through a small, unlocked door in the perimeter wall. While walking through the grounds, he encounters a young woman who appears physically weak and terrified. She urges him to leave immediately, warning that \"they\" are coming and that no one can help her. As Bobby retreats, he hides in the bushes to avoid a man walking down the path. After the man passes, Bobby realizes that the woman he encountered is the same person depicted in a mysterious missing photograph.",
